							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/lisagailcollins/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Lisa-Gail-Collins-100x100.jpeg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Lisa-Gail-Collins.jpeg 2x" alt="Lisa Gail Collins" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/lisagailcollins/">Lisa Gail Collins</a></h6>
										Lisa Gail Collins is the author of <em>Stitching Love and Loss: A Gee’s Bend Quilt</em> and Professor of Art and Director of American Studies on the Sarah Gibson Blanding Chair at Vassar College. Her other books include <em>The Art of History: African American Women Artists Engage the Past</em> and <em>New Thoughts on the Black Arts Movement</em> (coedited with Margo Natalie Crawford).																			</div>
								</div><br class="clear"/><br/>
							</div>
							<br class="clear"/>
						</div>
